{
  "answer": "In Mirza Ghalib's ghazal titled *Aah ko chahiye ik umr asar hote tak*, the opening couplet states that a sigh (*aah*) requires an entire age or lifetime (*umr*) to take effect or find its mark (*asar hote tak*).[^1]\n\nThis sets the theme of prolonged suffering and patience amid unrequited love, echoed throughout the poem in images of enduring dark nights of tresses, separation until Judgment Day, and dewdrops fading slowly under the sun.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch.3 \"Aah ko chahiye ik umr asar hote tak\", [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/03-aah-ko-chahiye-ik-umr-asar-hote-tak/translation/#p-0733e9).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch.3 \"Aah ko chahiye ik umr asar hote tak\", [chapter](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/03-aah-ko-chahiye-ik-umr-asar-hote-tak/translation/).",
